            <p>The CSS border-radius property defines the radius of an element's corners.</p>
 </div>

                <button type="button" class="collapsible">CSS Border Images                    ↓</button>
                <div class="content">
                  <p style=" background-image: url('https://cdn.donmai.us/original/8b/21/__gawr_gura_and_bloop_hololive_and_1_more_drawn_by_quasarcake__8b210dad0a6bb3e795dcad62b547efa6.jpg');">The border-image property takes the image and slices it into nine sections, like a tic-tac-toe board. It then places the corners at the corners, and the middle sections are repeated or stretched as you specify.

                    Note: For border-image to work, the element also needs the border property set!
                  </p>
 </div>
