<button type="button" class="collapsible">CSS Tooltips  ↓</button>
<div class="content">

  <p>Tooltips display text (or other content) when you hover over an HTML element. The w3-tooltip class defines the element to hover over (the tooltip container). The w3-text class defines the tooltip text.</p>
</div>
  <button type="button" class="collapsible">CSS Images  ↓</button>
<div class="content">
<p>CSS Images is a module of CSS that defines what types of images can be used (the image type, containing URLs, gradients and other types of images), how to resize them and how they, and other replaced content, interact with the different layout models.</p>
